Description: Extending a helpful hand for the health professional for over 25 years!
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Baron Medical is a Brooklyn, New York-based medical supply retailer. The company provides medical equipment to doctors, nurses, hospital workers and other healthcare professionals.   Customers need high-quality medical equipment to properly diagnose and treat their patients and Baron Medical is committed to providing them with exactly that. The company carefully selects its product inventory to ensure it is of the highest quality. Additionally, products are listed on the company’s website with detailed specifications, making it easy for customers to learn more about each item and find exactly what they need.   Product Offerings and Brands The company carries a wide range of medical diagnostic products, designed to meet the varying needs of its client base. General product offerings include stethoscopes, blood pressure monitors, thermometers and diagnostic equipment. Additionally, the company plans to expand its product offerings in the future to include scrubs, lab coats and additional medical equipment designed to meet the ever-changing needs of its customer base.   Baron Medical prides itself on working with medical manufacturers of the highest quality, ensuring the company only sells top quality products. The company only works with a small number of carefully selected manufacturers, including: ·   	3M Littman ·   	ADC ·   	Graham Field ·   	Prestige Medical ·   	Riester ·   	Welch Allyn Additionally, the company offers engraving on Littmann stethoscopes, allowing healthcare professionals to add a small, personalized touch to their diagnostic equipment. A name or short message can be added to the device for a small fee to make it unique.   Company History Baron Medical has been serving its loyal customers for more than four decades. The company has established itself as a leading supplier of diagnostic medical equipment, offering superior service and brand names that customers know and trust. It has always been a goal of the company to keep up with the latest medical technology, to provide customers with the best products on the market at the most reasonable prices.   Outstanding Customer Service The company offers outstanding service to its valued customers. Baron Medical ships to all locations in the United States and Canada. In fact, they offer free shipping and free returns on all orders of $99 or more and competitive flat rate shipping of $7.95 on all other orders. Orders are all shipped within one to three business days, ensuring customers get the equipment they need in a timely manner.   Baron Medical has a very generous return policy, to ensure customers are satisfied with every purchase. The company will provide a full refund for most unused items if returned within 50 days of purchase. In the rare instance that a customer receives the wrong item or a damaged product, they always pay for the return shipping and ensure the correct item is shipped as soon as possible.   Contact Information Customers with questions, comments and concerns can speak to a company representative by phone at 1-855-339-6626 or email at info@baronmedical.com. Customer service associates are on hand from 10am to 5:30pm EST from Monday through Thursday and from 10am to 2pm EST on Friday.

Description: The Ohio Heart and Vascular Center, Inc. was founded in 1995
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The Ohio Heart and Vascular Center, Inc. was founded in 1995 through the merger of five of the highest quality cardiovascular practices in the Greater Cincinnati area. The goal of this merger was to create a larger unified geographically diverse practice organization that would provide the opportunities to improve the delivery and quality of cardiovascular care to their patients. Specifically, they wanted to have a group large enough to support the subspecialty expertise and program development that would provide a level of care previously unavailable in their region. Over the past 16 years, the results of this endeavor have exceeded even their most optimistic initial projections. They have grown in size from their initial 17 founding partners to 40 cardiovascular physicians and surgeons. They have initiated subspecialty programs in cardiac electrophysiology (arrhythmias and pacemaker devices), coronary intervention (angioplasty and stents), peripheral vascular disease, congestive heart failure, cardiac surgery, and advanced cardiac imaging. These programs are not only the largest and most comprehensive physician-group based subspecialty programs in their area, but have each introduced many previously unavailable cutting edge technological advances in the diagnosis and treatment of heart disease. Each of these subspecialty sections of their group has achieved national and international recognition for their contributions to new clinical knowledge and to the evaluation of new techniques. Through their relationship with the Lindner Center for Clinical Research, they are able to bring to their patients the newest and most promising treatment modalities well before they are available to the general public. They are one of the few groups in the country to have incorporated high quality cardiovascular surgeons so that the full range of cardiac treatment modalities can be offered to their patients “under one roof” facilitating the most appropriate treatment decisions for each patient. Their growth as a physician organization has come largely from their ability to recruit some of the finest young medical talent from the premier training programs, from all over the country. They have been attracted by the unique practice and subspecialty opportunities that can only be offered by a group of their size and scope. Many have brought with them new skills and innovations that had not previously been available in their community. By increasing their size, they have also been able to provide more comprehensive care to the many geographically diverse areas they serve by providing as much care as possible in offices close to the patients’ own community. They strive to maintain a compassionate and personal doctor-patient relationship while simultaneously providing the patient easy access to their subspecialty services. They currently have offices in eighteen communities and are integrally involved with nine hospital systems in the Southern Ohio and Southeastern Indiana regions. By working closely with these local and regional hospital systems, they strive to provide the most technologically advanced care in the most convenient, accessible, and seamless way possible. None of this would be possible without their incredibly talented and dedicated non-physician medical and administrative staff of over 225 employees. Their size and organization have allowed us to recruit and maintain the best people available and their skill and caring greatly facilitate their physicians’ ability to deliver the best cardiovascular care in the most efficient manner possible. The Ohio Heart and Vascular Center, Inc. is proud to serve the cardiovascular needs of the Greater Cincinnati area. They are also proud of the many innovations, skilled personnel, and organizational benefits they have contributed to their community over the past 16 years. They pledge to continue in their mission to provide the most technologically advanced and effective care to the greatest number of people in the most easily accessible and caring environment possible.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Ansel Capital Partners was founded in 2007 in response to the growing need for organized angel investor efforts. Due to the widening gap in the capital markets, there is a shortage of funding available at the seed stage ($250K-$5M). This funding gap represents a great opportunity for investment in companies with substantial growth potential but an inability to attract or lack of desire to engage venture capital. ACP members invest their time, talent, and money in supporting companies with solid business models and their efforts to grow successfully. Angel financing is the lifeblood of growing companies. Ansel Capital Partners organizes the resources of the angels by streamlining the deal flow. We present monthly reviews of two targeted, prescreened companies that are matched to investor's interests. Each month we target one of the three investment types: Medical devices, Health care services, and Healthcare IT. Materials are summarized and distributed prior to each meeting.  	 	 	  Ansel Capital Partners is a member of the Angel Capital Association. The Angel Capital Association is the professional alliance of angel groups in North America, providing professional development, best practices, networking and collaboration opportunities for angel investors who belong to member angel groups.
